Claims Claims: 1. A composite comprising: a) a plastic substrate; and b) an electrical insulator layer disposed on the plastic substrate and comprising boron nitride nanotubes (BNNTs). 2. The composite of claim 1, wherein the BNNTs are modified BNNTs. 3. The composite of claim 2, wherein the modified BNNTs are wrapped with a polymer or coated with a ligand or a surfactant. 4. The composite of claim 2, wherein the modified BNNTs are polymer-wrapped BNNTs. 5. The composite of claim 3, wherein the polymer- wrapped BNNTs are wrapped in regiorandom poly(3-hexylthiophene-2,5-diyl) (rra-P3HT). 6. The composite of any one of claims 2 to 5, wherein the modified BNNTs are single- walled. 7. The composite of any one of claims 2 to 5, wherein the modified BNNTs are multi- walled. 8. The composite of claim 2, wherein the modified BNNTs comprise pendant hydroxyl (OH) and amino (NH 2 ) functional groups covalently bonded to an outer surface of the BNNT. 9. The composite of claim 8, wherein a ratio of pendant OH groups to NH 2 groups is about 2: 1. 10. The composite of claim 8 or 9, wherein the number of pendant OH groups is between about 1 OH per 6 BN-units and about 1 OH per 240 BN-units. 11. The composite of claim 10, wherein the number of pendant OH groups is between about 1 OH per 12 BN-units and about 1 OH per 124 BN-units. 12. The composite of claim 11, wherein the number of pendant OH groups is about 1 OH per 18 BN-units. 13. The composite of any one of claims 8 to 12, wherein the modified BNNTs are single- walled. 14. The composite of any one of claims 8 to 12, wherein the modified BNNTs are multi- walled. 15. The composite of any one of claims 3-5, wherein the polymer comprises a conjugated polymer. 16. The composite of claim 15, wherein the conjugated polymer is a polythiophene comprising at least one alkyl side chain, a polyfluorene comprising at least one alkyl side chain, a poly(fluorene-co-pyridine) comprising at least one alkyl side chain, or a poly(thiophene-co-fluorene) comprising at least one alkyl side chain. 17. The composite of claim 15 or 16, wherein the polymer is: (a) a polythiophene of Formula I: (I) wherein R a is C 4-24 alkyl and n is an integer from 10-200; 

 (b) a polyfluorene of Formula II: (II) wherein each R b is independently C 6 -24 alkyl and m is an integer from 10-100; or (c) a poly(fluorene-co-pyridine) of Formula III: (Ill) wherein each R c is independently C 6-24 alkyl and q is an integer from 10-100. 18. The composite of claim 17, wherein R is n-hexyl or n-octadecyl, R b is n-octyl or n- octadecyl; and R c is n-octadecyl. 19. The composite of claim 1, wherein the BNNTs are unmodified BNNTs. 20. The composite of any one of claims 1 to 19, wherein the substrate is selected from the group consisting of: polycarbonate (PC), polyethylene terephthalate (PET), polyethylene terephthalate glycol (PETG), polyethylene naphthalate (PEN), polyimide, and a polyester. 21. The composite of any one of claims 1 to 19, wherein the substrate comprises polyethylene terephthalate (PET). 22. A process for printing electronics, the process comprising sintering a metallic ink on the composite of any one of claims 1 to 21. 23. The process of claim 22, wherein the sintering is photonic or thermal. 24. The process of claim 23, wherein the sintering is intense pulsed light sintering. 25. The process of any one of claims 22 to 24, wherein the metallic ink comprises silver, copper or nickel. 26. The process of claim 25 wherein the metallic ink comprises silver. 27. The process of any one of claims 22 to 26, wherein the metallic ink is a molecular ink, a particulate ink or an ink comprising flakes, or any mixture thereof. 28. The process of claim 27, wherein the metallic ink is a molecular ink. 29. The process of claim 27, wherein the metallic ink is a particulate ink of nanoparticles comprising a metal. 30. The process of claim 27, wherein the metallic ink is a mixture of: a particulate ink of nanoparticles comprising a metal; and a molecular ink. 31. The process of claim 29 or 30, wherein the metal is silver, copper or nickel. 32. The process of claim 31, wherein the metal is silver. 33. The process of claim 27, wherein the metallic ink comprises flakes of silver. 34. The process of claim 27, wherein the metallic ink is a mixture of an ink comprising flakes of silver and a molecular ink. 35. The process of any one of claims 22 to 34, wherein prior to sintering, the metallic ink is applied to the composite by screen, inkjet, microplotting, flexure-gravure, offset printing or stencil printing. 36. Use of a coating on a plastic substrate for reduction of heat transfer to the substrate during sintering, wherein the coating comprises boron nitride nanotubes (BNNTs). 37. The use of claim 36, wherein the BNNTs are modified BNNTs. 38. The use of claim 37, wherein the modified BNNTs are wrapped with a polymer or coated with a ligand or a surfactant. 39. The use of claim 37, wherein the modified BNNTs are polymer-wrapped BNNTs. 40. The use of claim 39, wherein the polymer-wrapped BNNTs are wrapped in regiorandom poly(3-hexylthiophene-2,5-diyl) (rra-P3HT). 41. The use of any one of claims 36 to 40, wherein the modified BNNTs are single-walled. 42. The use of any one of claims 36 to 40, wherein the modified BNNTs are multi-walled. 43. The use of claim 37, wherein the modified BNNTs comprise pendant hydroxyl (OH) and amino (NH2) functional groups covalently bonded to a surface of the modified BNNTs. 44. The use of claim 43, wherein a ratio of pendant OH groups to NH2 groups is about 2:1. 45. The use of claim 43 or 44, wherein the number of pendant OH groups is between about 1 OH per 6 BN-units and about 1 OH per 240 BN-units. 46. The use of claim 45, wherein the number of pendant OH groups is between about 1 OH per 12 BN-units and about 1 OH per 124 BN-units. 47. The use of claim 46, wherein the number of pendant OH groups is about 1 OH per 18 BN-units. 48. The use of any one of claims 43 to 47, wherein the BNNTs are single-walled. 49. The use of any one of claims 43 to 47, wherein the BNNTs are multi-walled. 50. The use of claim 38 or 39, wherein the polymer comprises a conjugated polymer. 51. The use of claim 50, wherein the conjugated polymer is a polythiophene comprising at least one alkyl side chain, a polyfluorene comprising at least one alkyl side chain, a poly(fluorene-co-pyridine) comprising at least one alkyl side chain, or a poly(thiophene- co-fluorene) comprising at least one alkyl side chain. 52. The use of claim 50 or 51, wherein the conjugated polymer is: (a) a polythiophene of Formula I : (I) wherein R a is C 4-24 alkyl and n is an integer from 10-200; 

