ss of claim 69, wherein the metallic ink comprises silver. 71. The process of any one of claims 56 to 70, wherein the metallic ink is a molecular ink, a particulate ink or an ink comprising flakes, or any mixture thereof. 72. The process of claim 71, wherein the metallic ink is a molecular ink. 73. The process of claim 71, wherein the metallic ink is a particulate ink of nanoparticles comprising a metal. 74. The process of claim 71, wherein the metallic ink is a mixture of: a particulate ink of nanoparticles comprising a metal; and a molecular ink. 75. The process of claim 73 or 74, wherein the metal is silver, copper or nickel. 76. The process of claim 75, wherein the metal is silver. 77. The process of claim 76 wherein the metallic ink comprises flakes of silver. 78. The process of claim 76, wherein the metallic ink is a mixture of an ink comprising flakes of silver and a molecular ink. 79. The process of any one of claims 56 to 78, wherein prior to sintering, the metallic ink is applied to the composite by screen, inkjet, microplotting, flexure-gravure, offset printing or stencil printing. 80. The process of any one of claim 56 to 79, wherein providing the plastic substrate comprises providing a substrate fabricated from one of the following: polycarbonate (PC), polyethylene terephthalate (PET), polyethylene terephthalate glycol PETG, polyethylene naphthalate (PEN), polyimide, and a polyester.
